06/03/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Various politicians must leave behind differences and unite behind reforms that will lead to NATO membership, Daniel Fried, US assistant secretary of state for European and Eurasian affairs, said in an interview for Voice of America on Monday (March 5th). He stressed that Macedonia does not have much time to prove its membership capability, as the next NATO summit is about a year away.
In other news Monday, the leader of main ethnic Albanian party, the Democratic Union for Integration (DUI), Ali Ahmeti, said he had accepted an invitation to meet this week with Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski. International community envoys will also attend the talks, aimed at leading to the resumption of dialogue between the ruling coalition and the opposition.. (Vecer - 06/03/07; Makfax, A1 TV - 07/03/07)
